
VM versus VS
 
1- What is VM, how it is different form VS?
2- Options to use different machine types with different config depending on required computational power,
3- The option of monthly billing
4- Less maintenance than VS, preparing confluence pages is the key
5- To use VS, we really need comprehensive testing, since it has 1 year contract. A very Short-term benchmark is not enough reliable for choosing a config
6- VM is the way to go for now even if we want to switch to VS down the road
7- VS provides options for multiple users at the same time, while VM is for one
8- Risks and Considerations:
9- There is no risk of using VM, in terms of missing ADA servers, since ADA will be available all the time
10- The team should be cautious enough to shut down VM after usage
11- The team should be cautious enough and use VM only when required
12- The team should be cautious about choosing a VM that is compatible with their tasks, otherwise, if we use a very powerful machine for a simple task, we face with underperforming machine and a waste of money
 